title: NetApp Filer: NTP time offset
agents: netapp
catalog: hw/storagehw/netapp
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the NTP time synchronization of each NetApp node.

 It evaluates the time offset reported by the currently selected NTP server
 for the monitored node.

 This check relies on the private CLI passthrough endpoint ({/api/private/cli/cluster/time-service/ntp/status})
 to fetch the NTP status, as no public REST API is available. To enable this, ensure the monitoring user is
 assigned an ONTAP REST role with read access to this endpoint.

 Returns {CRIT} if no NTP server is available for the node, if no NTP server
 is currently selected, or if the selected NTP server provides no offset.

 Returns {WARN}/{CRIT} if the absolute NTP time offset is above the
 given levels.

 Please note: You need the Special Agent "NetApp via ONTAP REST Api" to
 retrieve the monitoring data from the device. The Special Agent itself can
 be configured by WATO.

item:
 Name of the node

discovery:
 One service is created for each node.
